name: $$NAME
description: <Disclaimer : PLEASE DO NOT RENAME OR DELETE THE FOLDER>. This is folder created by SumoLogic Jenkins Plugin for dashboards.

children.name: Jenkins - Overview
children.description: The Jenkins - Overview dashboard provides relation between job and Executors on a Jenkins master. Dashboard helps you to relate job run duration, status, physical memory, disk memory, unused machine.

panels.name: Outlier - Shutdown Events
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc "eventSource":"Shutdown" 
| _sourceHost as Master
| timeslice {{TimeSlice}}
| count as Count by _timeslice
| fillmissing timeslice({{TimeSlice}}) with 0 for Count
| outlier Count

panels.name: Console Log Errors Count
Queue Duration (Minutes)
Job Builds
Disk Memory
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "isOnline", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount, Onilne, NodeLabel nodrop
| where ExecutorsCount > 0 AND Onilne matches "true"
| where [subquery from=(-2d): $$jenkinslogsrc (*running on* OR *building on*)
| where _sourceName matches "{{JobName}}#{{BuildNumber}}"
| parse regex "Running on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| parse regex "Building on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| if (NodeName matches "Jenkins", "master", NodeName) as NodeName
| compose NodeName]
| where NodeName matches {{NodeName}} and NodeLabel matches {{NodeLabel}}
| json field=_raw "monitorData.DiskSpaceMonitor" as Disk_Space nodrop
| parse regex field=Disk_Space "(?<Disk_Space>.*?) (?<Unit>.*[A-Z]+)" nodrop
| where !isEmpty(Disk_Space)
| num(Disk_Space)
| if(Unit in ("MB", "Mb", "mb"), Disk_Space/1024, if(Unit in ("KB", "Kb", "kb"), Disk_Space/1024/1024, if(Unit in ("TB", "Tb", "tb"), Disk_Space*1024, Disk_Space))) as Disk_Space
| timeslice {{TimeSlice}}
| avg(Disk_Space) as Average, max(Disk_Space) as Maximum, min(Disk_Space) as Minimum by _timeslice
| fields _timeslice, Average, Minimum, Maximum
| compare with timeshift {{TimeCompare}}
| fillmissing timeslice({{TimeSlice}})
| fields - Maximum, Minimum, Minimum_1d, Maximum_1d

panels.name: System Log Errors Count
Jobs in Queue
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Queue_Event
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "jobName" as Name
| first(_raw) by Name, Master
| json field = _first "queueId", "queueTime", "isBlocked", "reasonForBlock", "isConcurrentBuild", "jobName", "jobURL" as %"Queue Id", %"Queue Time(sec)", Blocked, Reason, %"Concurrent Build", Name, URL nodrop
| tourl(URL, Name) as Name
| replace (URL, /\/[0-9]{1,}/, "") as URL
| where ![subquery : $$jenkinslogsrc "logType":"Job_Status"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "jobBuildURL" as URL
| replace (URL, /\/[0-9]{1,}/, "") as URL
| count by URL, Master
| compose URL, Master]
| count by Master, %"Queue Time(sec)", Name, Blocked, Reason
| fields - _count

panels.name: Physical Memory Use Percentage
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "isOnline", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount, Onilne, NodeLabel nodrop
| where ExecutorsCount > 0 AND Onilne matches "true"
| where [subquery from=(-2d): $$jenkinslogsrc (*running on* OR *building on*)
| where _sourceName matches "{{JobName}}#{{BuildNumber}}"
| parse regex "Running on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| parse regex "Building on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| if (NodeName matches "Jenkins", "master", NodeName) as NodeName
| compose NodeName]
| where NodeName matches {{NodeName}} and NodeLabel matches {{NodeLabel}}
| json "monitorData.SwapSpaceMonitor", "nodeLabel"  as SwapMemory, Node_Label nodrop
| parse field=SwapMemory "Memory:*  Swap:*" as Physical_Memory, Swap_Memory
| parse regex field=Physical_Memory "(?<Used_Memory>.*?)/(?<Total_Memory>.*?)[A-Z]"
| (Used_Memory/Total_Memory)*100 as Used_Memory
| timeslice {{TimeSlice}}
| avg(Used_Memory) as Average, max(Used_Memory) as Maximum, min(Used_Memory) as Minimum by _timeslice
| fields _timeslice, Average, Minimum, Maximum
| compare with timeshift {{TimeCompare}}
| fillmissing timeslice({{TimeSlice}})
| fields - Minimum, Maximum, Minimum_1d, Maximum_1d

panels.name: Executors
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| json "numberOfExecutors", "nodeName", "nodeLabel", "numberOfFreeExecutors", "eventTime" as Total_Executors, NodeName, NodeLabel, Free_Executors, Event_Time nodrop
| where NodeName matches {{NodeName}} and NodeLabel matches {{NodeLabel}}
| where [subquery from=(-2d): $$jenkinslogsrc (*running on* OR *building on*)
| where _sourceName matches "{{JobName}}#{{BuildNumber}}"
| parse regex "Running on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| parse regex "Building on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| if (NodeName matches "Jenkins", "master", NodeName) as NodeName
| compose NodeName]
| timeslice {{TimeSlice}}
| Total_Executors - Free_Executors as Busy_Executors
| first(Total_Executors) as Total_Executors, first(Busy_Executors) as Busy_Executors by NodeName, _timeslice
| where Busy_Executors >= 0
| sum(Total_Executors) as Total, sum(Busy_Executors) as Busy by _timeslice
| compare with timeshift {{TimeCompare}}
| fillmissing timeslice({{TimeSlice}})

panels.name: Job Duration (Minutes)
Machines
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| json "numberOfExecutors", "nodeName", "nodeLabel", "numberOfFreeExecutors", "eventTime" as Total_Executors, NodeName, NodeLabel, Free_Executors, Event_Time nodrop
| where NodeName matches {{NodeName}} and NodeLabel matches {{NodeLabel}}
| where Total_Executors > 0
| where [subquery from=(-2d): $$jenkinslogsrc (*running on* OR *building on*)
| where _sourceName matches "{{JobName}}#{{BuildNumber}}"
| parse regex "Running on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| parse regex "Building on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| if (NodeName matches "Jenkins", "master", NodeName) as NodeName
| compose NodeName]
| timeslice {{TimeSlice}}
| count_distinct (NodeName) as Total by _timeslice
| compare with timeshift {{TimeCompare}}
| fillmissing timeslice({{TimeSlice}})

panels.name: Unused Machines
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| json "numberOfExecutors", "nodeName", "nodeLabel", "numberOfFreeExecutors", "eventTime" as Total_Executors, NodeName, NodeLabel, Free_Executors, Event_Time nodrop
| where NodeName matches {{NodeName}} and NodeLabel matches {{NodeLabel}}
| where Total_Executors > 0
| where ![subquery from=(-2d): $$jenkinslogsrc (*running on* OR *building on*)
| where _sourceName matches "{{JobName}}#{{BuildNumber}}"
| parse regex "Running on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| parse regex "Building on (?<NodeName>.*) in" nodrop
| if (NodeName matches "Jenkins", "master", NodeName) as NodeName
| compose NodeName]
| timeslice {{TimeSlice}}
| count_distinct (NodeName) as Total by _timeslice
| compare with timeshift {{TimeCompare}}
| fillmissing timeslice({{TimeSlice}})

children.name: Job Monitoring
children.description: Job Monitoring dashboards helps you to monitor Job Run duration, Status, Slowest Jobs, failed jobs, failed Test cases along with the stack trace for failure, sailed stages along with the exact command of failure, source control management details along with commit information, job configuration changes and stage wise console logs.

children.name: Console Logs by Stages
children.description: Query to get console logs by Stages for a Job.
children.searchQuery:
$$jenkinslogsrc _sourceName={{Job_Name}}#*
| parse field=_raw "[*] *" as Log_Time, Log_Message
| trim (Log_Message)
| parse regex field=_sourceName "(?<Job_Name>.*?)#(?<Build_Number>[0-9]+)(?<Stage_Name>.*)" nodrop
| count by Log_Time, Job_Name, Build_Number, Stage_Name, Log_Message
| sort by Log_Time
| fields Log_Time, Job_Name, Build_Number, Stage_Name, Log_Message

children.name: Parse Stages for Job
children.description: Query to get all the stages for a Job.
children.searchQuery:
$$jenkinslogsrc Pipeline_Stages {{Job_Name}}
| json "name"
| where name = {{Job_Name}}
| json "stages" as StagesPipeline
| parse regex field = StagesPipeline "(?<json_added_blob>\{[^\}]+(?:\}\}|\}))" multi
| json field=json_added_blob "startTime", "stageId", "name", "duration", "status", "pauseDuration", "id", "steps", "error" as Start_Time, Stage_Id, Stage_Name, Stage_Duration, Stage_Status, Stage_Pause_Duration, ID, Steps, Error nodrop
| count  by Start_Time, Stage_Id, Stage_Name, Stage_Duration, Stage_Status, Stage_Pause_Duration, ID, Steps, Error
| sort by Start_Time
| fields - _count, ID

children.name: Test Cases Comparison by Builds
children.description: Query to Compare test results by Builds for a job.

children.name: Test Cases Parsing
children.description: Query to get all the test cases for a Job.

children.name: System Monitoring
children.description: System Monitoring dashboards helps you to monitor changes related to Jenkins Configuration, Job Configuration, health of the Jenkins Master, performance of Job Queue, performance of Job Run Duration, health of all the slaves available within the Jenkins Master.

children.name: Jenkins - Audit
children.description: The Jenkins - Audit dashboard provides insights into all authentication activities. Panels display information on Jenkins system and job configuration changes, as well as job run activities.

panels.name: Most Changed Configuration
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Audit_Event
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "userName", "auditEventType", "userId", "message", "eventTime" as UserName, Event, UserId, Message, Time nodrop
| where Event in ("Config_Change")
| parse regex "file (?<Item_Name>.*?).xml"
| concat(Item_Name, ".xml") as ItemName
| where !(ItemName matches "jobs/*")
| count as Count by ItemName
| sort by Count
| limit 5

panels.name: User Authentication
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Audit_Event
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "userName", "auditEventType", "userId", "message", "eventTime" as UserName, Event, UserId, Message, Time nodrop
| where Event in ("User_Login", "User_Logout", "User_Login_Failure")
| count as Count by Time, Master, Event, UserName, UserId, Message
| sort by Time
| fields - Count

panels.name: Configuration Change
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Audit_Event
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "userName", "auditEventType", "userId", "message", "eventTime" as UserName, Event, UserId, Message, Time nodrop
| where Event in ("Config_Change")
| json "fileDetails.Current_File_Data", "fileDetails.Old_File_Data" as Current_File_Data, Old_File_Data nodrop
| base64Decode(Current_File_Data) as Current_File_Data
| base64Decode(Old_File_Data) as Old_File_Data
| count as Count by Time, Master, Event, UserName, UserId, Message
| sort by Time
| fields - Count

panels.name: Most changed Jobs Configuration
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Audit_Event
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "userName", "auditEventType", "userId", "message", "eventTime" as UserName, Event, UserId, Message, Time nodrop
| where Event in ("Config_Change")
| parse regex "file (?<ItemName>.*?).xml"
| concat(ItemName, ".xml") as ItemName
| where ItemName matches "jobs/*"
| parse field=ItemName "jobs/*/config.xml" as JobName
| count as Count by JobName
| sort by Count
| limit 5

panels.name: Jobs Trend
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Audit_Event
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "userName", "auditEventType", "userId", "message", "eventTime" as UserName, Event, UserId, Message, Time nodrop
| where Event in ("Job_Started", "Job_Aborted", "Job_Finished")
| timeslice 10m
| count as Count by _timeslice, Event
| transpose row _timeslice column Event
| fillmissing timeslice(10m)

panels.name: Job Activities
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Audit_Event
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "userName", "auditEventType", "userId", "message", "eventTime" as UserName, Event, UserId, Message, Time nodrop
| where Event in ("Job_Started", "Job_Aborted", "Job_Finished")
| count as Count by Time, Master, Event, UserName, UserId, Message
| sort by Time
| fields - Count

panels.name: Jenkins Item Change
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Audit_Event
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "userName", "auditEventType", "userId", "message", "eventTime" as UserName, Event, UserId, Message, Time nodrop
| where Event in ("Created", "Deleted", "Updated", "Copied", "Location_Changed")
| count as Count by Time, Master, Event, UserName, UserId, Message
| sort by Time
| fields - Count

panels.name: User Events
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Audit_Event
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "userName", "auditEventType", "userId", "message", "eventTime" as UserName, Event, UserId, Message, Time nodrop
| count as Count by UserId, Event
| transpose row UserId column Event
| limit 5

children.name: Jenkins - Job Health
children.description: The Jenkins - Job Health dashboard provides insight into the health of the Jenkins Jobs. Panels display information on Jenkins Job Count, Jenkins Job Run Duration, Jenkins Queue Information and Garbage Collections.

metricsQueries.query: $$jenkinslogsrc *.vm.gc.*.time | parse field=_rawName "*.vm.gc.*.time" as prefix, name | eval _value/60

children.name: Jenkins - Master Health
children.description: The Jenkins - Master Health dashboard provides insight into the health of the Jenkins master. Panels display information on shutdown events, Jenkins system logs, and metrics events such as CPU, memory,  jenkins threads, jenkins executors.

panels.name: Jenkins System Logs
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Jenkins_Log
| json "threadId", "logType", "logLevel", "logMessage", "logSource", "eventTime", "logStackTrace" as %"Thread ID", %"Log Type", %"Log Level", %"Log Message", %"Log Source", %"Event Time", %"Log Stack Trace" nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| where Master matches {{Master}} AND %"Log Level" matches {{LogLevel}} AND %"Log Message" matches {{LogMessage}}
| count by Master, %"Event Time", %"Thread ID", %"Log Type", %"Log Level", %"Log Source", %"Log Message", %"Log Stack Trace"
| sort by %"Event Time"
| fields - _count

panels.name: Shutdown Events
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc "eventSource":"Shutdown" 
| _sourceHost as Master
| timeslice 10m
| count as Count by _timeslice, Master
| transpose row _timeslice column Master
| fillmissing timeslice(10m)

children.name: Jenkins - Node Health
children.description: The Jenkins - Node Health dashboard provides insights into the health of all the nodes present on the Jenkins master. Panels display information on disk usage, physical Memory usage, as well as free and busy executors.

panels.name: Offline Nodes
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount,NodeLabel
| first(_raw) as Message by NodeName, Master
| where ![subquery:$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master 
| compose NodeName, Master]
| json field=Message "nodeName", "monitorData.ArchitectureMonitor", "monitorData.ClockMonitor" ,"monitorData.ResponseTimeMonitor", "monitorData.DiskSpaceMonitor", "monitorData.TemporarySpaceMonitor", "monitorData.SwapSpaceMonitor", "isIdle", "isOnline", "nodeURL", "nodeLabel"  as Node_Name, Architecture, Clock, Reponse_Time, Disk_Space, Temporary_Space, SwapMemory, Idle, Online, URL, Label nodrop
| where Online = "false"
| count as Count by Online

panels.name: Jenkins Nodes
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount,NodeLabel
| _sourceHost as Master
| first(_raw) as Message by NodeName, Master
| where ![subquery:$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master 
| compose NodeName, Master]
| json field=Message "nodeName", "monitorData.ArchitectureMonitor", "monitorData.ClockMonitor" ,"monitorData.ResponseTimeMonitor", "monitorData.DiskSpaceMonitor", "monitorData.TemporarySpaceMonitor", "monitorData.SwapSpaceMonitor", "isIdle", "isOnline", "nodeURL", "nodeLabel"  as %"Node Name", Architecture, Clock, %"Reponse Time", %"Disk Space", Temporary_Space, SwapMemory, Idle, Online, URL, %"Node Label" nodrop
| if(Idle matches "true", "false", "true") as Busy
| parse field=SwapMemory "Memory:*  Swap:*" as Physical_Memory, Swap_Memory
| parse regex field=Physical_Memory "(?<Used_Physical_Memory>.*?)/(?<Total_Physical_Memory>.*?)(?<Unit_Phy>[A-Z]+)"
| num(Used_Physical_Memory) | num(Total_Physical_Memory)
| (Used_Physical_Memory/Total_Physical_Memory)*100 as Used_Physical_Memory
| parse regex field=Swap_Memory "(?<Used_Swap_Memory>.*?)/(?<Total_Swap_Memory>.*?)(?<Unit_Swap>[A-Z]+)"
| num(Used_Swap_Memory) | num(Total_Swap_Memory)
| (Used_Swap_Memory/Total_Swap_Memory)*100 as Used_Swap_Memory
| if(Total_Physical_Memory=0, "0 %", format("%.2f %s",Used_Physical_Memory, "%")) as %"Used Physical Memory"
| if(Total_Swap_Memory=0, "0 %", format("%.2f %s",Used_Swap_Memory, "%")) as %"Used Swap Memory"
| replace(URL, "(", "%28") as URL
| replace(URL, ")", "%29") as URL
| tourl(URL, %"Node Name") as URL
| count by Master, %"Node Name", %"Node Label", Busy, Online, Architecture, Clock, %"Reponse Time", %"Used Physical Memory", %"Used Swap Memory", %"Disk Space", URL
| fields - _count

panels.name: Busy Nodes
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount,NodeLabel
| first(_raw) as Message by NodeName, Master
| where ![subquery:$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master 
| compose NodeName, Master]
| json field=Message "nodeName", "monitorData.ArchitectureMonitor", "monitorData.ClockMonitor" ,"monitorData.ResponseTimeMonitor", "monitorData.DiskSpaceMonitor", "monitorData.TemporarySpaceMonitor", "monitorData.SwapSpaceMonitor", "isIdle", "isOnline", "nodeURL", "nodeLabel"  as %"Node Name", Architecture, Clock, Reponse_Time, Disk_Space, Temporary_Space, SwapMemory, Idle, Online, URL, %"Node Label" nodrop
| if(Idle matches "true", "false", "true") as Busy
| where busy = "true"
| count as Count by Busy

panels.name: Physical Memory
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "isOnline", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount, Onilne, NodeLabel nodrop
| where ExecutorsCount > 0 AND Onilne matches "true"
| first(_raw) as Message by NodeName, Master
| where ![subquery:$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master 
| compose NodeName, Master]
| concat(Master, "-", NodeName) as NodeName
| json field=Message "monitorData.SwapSpaceMonitor", "nodeLabel"  as SwapMemory, Node_Label nodrop
| parse field=SwapMemory "Memory:*  Swap:*" as Physical_Memory, Swap_Memory
| parse regex field=Physical_Memory "(?<Used_Memory>.*?)/(?<Total_Memory>.*?)[A-Z]"
| Used_Memory/Total_Memory as Used_Memory
| 1 - Used_Memory as Free_Memory
| avg(Used_Memory) as %"Used Memory", avg(Free_Memory) as %"Free Memory" by NodeName

panels.name: Recent Builds
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Job_Status
| json "nodeName", "name", "result", "jobBuildURL", "number" as NodeName, JobName, Result, jobBuildURL, Number nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| tourl(jobBuildURL, JobName) as JobName
| JobName as %"Job Name"
| NodeName as %"Node Name"
| count by Master, %"Node Name", %"Job Name", Number, Result
| fields - _count

panels.name: Node Events
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc ("Computer_Online" OR "Computer_Offline" OR "Computer_Temp_Online" OR "Computer_Temp_Offline" OR "Launch_Failure")
| json "nodeName", "eventSource", "eventTime", "nodeLabel", "numberOfExecutors", "nodeURL" as NodeName, Event, Time, NodeLabel, Executors, Node_URL nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| NodeName as %"Node Name"
| NodeLabel as %"Node Label"
| replace(Node_URL, "(", "%28") as Node_URL
| replace(Node_URL, ")", "%29") as Node_URL
| tourl(Node_URL, %"Node Name") as %"Node URL"
| count as Count by Time, Master, Event, %"Node Name", %"Node Label", Executors, %"Node URL"
| sort by Time
| fields - Count

panels.name: Offline Nodes
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc ("Computer_Offline")
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, NodeLabel nodrop
| _sourceHost as Jenkins_Master
| concat ("Master=",Master," Node=", NodeName) as %"Master Node Name" 
| timeslice 10m
| count as Count by _timeslice, %"Master Node Name"
| transpose row _timeslice column %"Master Node Name"
| fillmissing timeslice(10m)

panels.name: Recently Removed Nodes
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by Time, NodeName, Master 
| sort by Time
| fields - Count

panels.name: Idle Nodes
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount,NodeLabel
| first(_raw) as Message by NodeName, Master
| where ![subquery:$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master 
| compose NodeName, Master]
| json field=Message "nodeName", "monitorData.ArchitectureMonitor", "monitorData.ClockMonitor" ,"monitorData.ResponseTimeMonitor", "monitorData.DiskSpaceMonitor", "monitorData.TemporarySpaceMonitor", "monitorData.SwapSpaceMonitor", "isIdle", "isOnline", "nodeURL", "nodeLabel"  as %"Node Name", Architecture, Clock, Reponse_Time, Disk_Space, Temporary_Space, SwapMemory, Idle, Online, URL, %"Node Label" nodrop
| if(Idle matches "true", "false", "true") as Busy
| where busy = "false"
| count as Count by Busy

panels.name: Available Disk Space (GB)
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "isOnline", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount, Onilne, NodeLabel nodrop
| where ExecutorsCount > 0 AND Onilne matches "true"
| where ![subquery:$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master 
| compose NodeName, Master]
| concat(Master, "-", NodeName) as %"Node Name"
| json field=_raw "monitorData.DiskSpaceMonitor" as Disk_Space nodrop
| parse regex field=Disk_Space "(?<Disk_Space>.*?) (?<Unit>.*[A-Z]+)" nodrop
| num(Disk_Space)
| if(Unit in ("MB", "Mb", "mb"), Disk_Space/1024, if(Unit in ("KB", "Kb", "kb"), Disk_Space/1024/1024, if(Unit in ("TB", "Tb", "tb"), Disk_Space*1024, Disk_Space))) as Disk_Space
| timeslice 10m
| avg(Disk_Space) as Disk_Space by _timeslice, %"Node Name"
| transpose row _timeslice column %"Node Name"

panels.name: Launch Failures
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc ("Launch_Failure")
| json "nodeName", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, NodeLabel nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| concat ("Master=",Master," Node=", NodeName) as %"Master Node Name" 
| timeslice 10m
| count as Count by _timeslice, %"Master Node Name"
| transpose row _timeslice column %"Master Node Name"
| fillmissing timeslice(10m)

panels.name: Online Nodes
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| _sourceHost as Master
| json "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors", "nodeLabel" as NodeName, ExecutorsCount,NodeLabel
| first(_raw) as Message by NodeName, Master
| where ![subquery:$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master 
| compose NodeName, Master]
| json field=Message "nodeName", "monitorData.ArchitectureMonitor", "monitorData.ClockMonitor" ,"monitorData.ResponseTimeMonitor", "monitorData.DiskSpaceMonitor", "monitorData.TemporarySpaceMonitor", "monitorData.SwapSpaceMonitor", "isIdle", "isOnline", "nodeURL", "nodeLabel"  as Node_Name, Architecture, Clock, Reponse_Time, Disk_Space, Temporary_Space, SwapMemory, Idle, Online, URL, Label nodrop
| where Online = "true"
| count as Count by Online

panels.name: Executors
panels.queryString:
$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"updated"
| json "numberOfExecutors", "nodeName", "nodeLabel", "numberOfFreeExecutors", "eventTime" as Total_Executors, NodeName, NodeLabel, Free_Executors, Event_Time nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| concat(Master, "-",NodeName) as NodeName
| Total_Executors - Free_Executors as Busy_Executors
| first(Total_Executors) as Total_Executors, first(Free_Executors) as Free_Executors, first(Busy_Executors) as Busy_Executors by NodeName
| where Busy_Executors >= 0
| where ![subquery:$$jenkinslogsrc Periodic_Update "nodeStatus":"removed"
| json "eventTime", "nodeName", "numberOfExecutors" as Time, NodeName, ExecutorsCount nodrop
| _sourceHost as Master
| count as Count by NodeName, Master
| concat(Master, "-",NodeName) as NodeName
| compose NodeName]
| NodeName as %"Node Name"
| avg(Free_Executors) as %"Free Executors", avg(Busy_Executors) as %"Busy Executors" by %"Node Name"
| fields %"Node Name", %"Free Executors", %"Busy Executors"
